# Mica — environment configuration
#
# Copy to `.env` in one of two locations (the server loads both, with the
# workspace one taking precedence over the repo one; ambient env wins over
# both):
#   <PROJECT_DIR>/.env   — typical for Docker deployments (workspace root)
#   <repo-root>/.env     — typical for local dev checkouts
#
# Nothing is required — everything has sensible defaults. Set only what you
# want to override.

# ─── OpenRouter (cloud-model fallback for chat cards) ────────────────────
# The key is also settable per-project via the chat card's gear icon, which
# wins over this. Stored then in <project>/.mica/config.json.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-…
# Default model used when a chat card is set to provider=openrouter and
# the card settings don't pin a specific model.
# OPENROUTER_DEFAULT_MODEL=anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet

# ─── Ports ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MICA_PORT=3002              # backend API
# MICA_FRONTEND_PORT=5173     # vite dev server

# ─── Local llama-server (the default chat model) ─────────────────────────
# MICA_DISABLE_LLAMA=1        # skip local llama-server entirely (OpenRouter-only)
# LLAMA_HF_REPO=unsloth/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-GGUF
# LLAMA_HF_FILE=Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-UD-Q6_K_XL.gguf
# LLAMA_MMPROJ=/path/to/mmproj-F16.gguf    # override auto-detect
# MODEL_PATH=/absolute/path/to/your.gguf   # bypass HF resolution entirely
# LLAMA_CTX_SIZE=65536        # per-slot context (KV = np × this)
# LLAMA_N_PARALLEL=3          # parallel decoding slots
# LLAMA_CACHE_RAM=16384       # host-memory prompt cache (MiB). "0" disables, "-1" unlimited.
# LLAMA_LOG_FILE=/workspaces/.mica-llama-server.log
# LLAMA_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8012    # override if llama-server runs elsewhere

# ─── Web search (qwen-code's web_search / web_fetch tools) ──────────────
# qwen-code ships built-in web_search and web_fetch tools but they're
# DISABLED unless a provider API key is set. Without one, the agent
# falls back to its training prior for any external fact-finding (CDN
# URL verification, library versions, recent docs) — usually
# plausible-but-stale. Set ONE of these to enable:
#
# TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-...              # https://tavily.com (1k free/mo)
# DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-...             # Alibaba's qwen-search
# GOOGLE_AI_STUDIO=...                 # Google Gemini's grounded-search
#
# qwen-code auto-detects whichever is set and routes web_search there.

# ─── Workspace ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PROJECT_DIR=/workspaces/testproj     # where projects live on disk
